Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper deals with structure-from-motion and registration of 3D point-sets, which are common problems in computer vision. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper's focus on rigid-motion synchronization has applications in robotics, particularly in robot perception and localization. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses Iteratively Reweighted Least Squares, a common optimization technique in machine learning. 
4. cs.GR (Graphics) - The paper's focus on 3D point-sets and rigid-motion synchronization has applications in computer graphics, particularly in animation and virtual reality. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper's focus on 3D point-sets and rigid-motion synchronization has applications in multimedia, particularly in 3D reconstruction and object tracking.
